CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 7, 1971, pg. 34 reads: "Mt. Carmel Models In Garden Fashion Fantasy - The beautiful lawn of Mt. Carmel Baptist Church, North Versailles Township, was the scene of a bright summer fashion fantasy. A brilliant array of ready-to-wear apparel for the young and the younger, and males as well, was on parade.  Smart models, pictured left to right are...Olena Moore, Brenda Powell, Marsha Herring, Mrs. Melvin Amos and her darling daughter, Shelley.-Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Olena Moore, Brenda Powell, Marsha Herring, Mrs. Melvin Amos and daughter, Shelley, standing outside of Mt. Carmel Baptist Church for Garden Fashion Fantasy, North Versailles
